Meeting Minutes (MoM)

Date: [Insert Date]
Attendees: [Your Name], [Manager Name]
Subject: Discussion on Upcoming Responsibilities, Learning Plan, and Deliverables

⸻

1. ML Monitoring – Learning & Ownership Plan
	•	I will be focusing on building end-to-end understanding of Machine Learning Monitoring over the next five months.
	•	The goal is to gain deep technical knowledge, covering all components, workflows, and operational aspects.
	•	I will work towards achieving clarity on each concept and aim to reach a stage where I have a comprehensive and detailed understanding of the ML monitoring framework.

⸻

2. Agentic AI – Knowledge Building & Sessions
	•	An initial knowledge-sharing session on Agentic AI is planned for mid-December.
	•	Two additional deep-dive sessions can be scheduled in January (next year) for broader team learning.
	•	In parallel, I will continue self-learning, including completing relevant Coursera courses and strengthening my understanding of Agentic AI fundamentals and use cases.

⸻

3. Onboarding & Collaboration with New Joiners
	•	I will work closely with new team members to support their onboarding to the Payment Screening process.
	•	This includes:
	•	Guiding them through tools, workflows, and operational responsibilities.
	•	Helping them with setting up accounts, access requests, and initial hands-on tasks.
	•	Ensuring they become comfortable and productive in the first few weeks.

⸻

4. Weekly JIRA Status Reporting
	•	I will share a weekly JIRA summary view, covering:
	•	Number of tickets closed by each member of the India team in the previous week.
	•	Ageing analysis to identify long-pending JIRAs.
	•	Any blockers or patterns that require attention.
	•	This report will be consistently maintained and shared with all relevant stakeholders.

⸻

5. LLM Enhancements – Exploration & Proposal
	•	I will work on identifying potential areas where LLMs can improve performance or optimize current processes.
	•	This includes exploring new integration opportunities, evaluating model improvements, and preparing proposals that highlight:
	•	Possible efficiency gains
	•	Automation opportunities
	•	Use cases beneficial for the Data Intelligence team
	•	These insights can help in future discussions and roadmap planning.

⸻

6. Out-of-Office (OOO) Planning & Handover
	•	All OOO requests will be planned and raised in advance, ensuring full visibility for the team.
	•	Before going on leave, I will share a detailed handover email, clearly listing:
	•	The status of ongoing JIRAs
	•	Pending actions or follow-ups
	•	Owners/Point of Contacts during my absence
	•	This will ensure continuity and smooth workflow while I am offline.

⸻

Next Steps
	•	Begin execution of the ML monitoring learning plan.
	•	Finalize dates for the December Agentic AI session.
	•	Start preparations for onboarding new joiners.
	•	Roll out the first weekly JIRA report from next cycle.

